
Some additional information on SuperCalc4 1.1:

1.  To run SuperCalc4 on a PC 3270 workstation, first perform the 
following DEBUG sequence (DEBUG is a DOS utility program; see your 
DOS manual for instructions):

	A>DEBUG SC4.COM
	-E 17C
	xxxx:017C    00.01
	-W
	writing DC80 bytes
	-Q
	A>

2.  To print the current date in headers and footers, use the symbol @.
To format this date with a user defined date format, follow the @ symbol 
with the corresponding format number.  For example:

	@3

prints the current date formatted as user-defined format #3.  See 
/Format,Define in Chapter 3 for a discussion of user-defined formats,
and refer to /Output for a discussion of the Output Options menu.